<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="519" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="122.[2013,2609,2336,2763]" pageId="122" pageNumber="519">
<taxonomicName authority="Stanley et al., 2015" authorityName="Stanley" authorityYear="2015" box="[2018,2260,2537,2566]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Crocidura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="122" pageNumber="519" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="munissii">Crocidura munissii</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[2393,2517,2537,2566]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Crocidura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="122" pageNumber="519" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monax">C. monax</taxonomicName>
clade. It was previously included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[2476,2609,2572,2605]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Crocidura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="122" pageNumber="519" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monax">C. monax</taxonomicName>
until it was described as a distinct species along with C. mdumai, to which it is a sister species phylogenetically. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
