<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="520" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="123.[157,1364,288,879]" pageId="123" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[159,509,647,676]" pageId="123" pageNumber="520">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Munissi’s White-toothed Shrew was considered conspecific with the Kilimanjaro White-toothed Shrew (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[172,308,730,755]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Crocidura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="123" pageNumber="536" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monax">C. monax</taxonomicName>
), which was classified as Data Deficient. It has a very restricted distribution and might be threatened by agricultural expansion and other forms of habitat destruction.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
